ents%20to%20benefit%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20have%20complained%20that%20such%20reports%20are%20costly%20and%20time-consuming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20fewer%20reports%20could%20impact%20white-collar%20jobs%2C%20from%20legal%20and%20accounting%20to%20communications.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20over%20quarterly%20earnings%20usually%20centers%20on%20companies%20and%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20but%20any%20disruption%20to%20the%20status%20quo%20could%20rattle%20an%20ecosystem%20full%20of%20white-collar%20workers%20plying%20their%20trade%20as%20lawyers%2C%20communications%20pros%2C%20and%20data%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ftrump-wants-company-earnings-change-6-months-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20asked%20the%20SEC%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20investigate%20whether%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-quarterly-reporting-plan-corporate-earnings-investors-retail-traders-investing-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efewer%20earnings%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20benefit%20companies.%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20save%20money%20and%20allow%20managers%20to%20focus%20on%20properly%20running%20their%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20administration's%20whiplash-inducing%20trade%20policies%2C%20corporate%20America%20agrees%20with%20the%20president.%20In%202019%2C%20after%20Trump%20first%20asked%20the%20SEC%20to%20explore%20this%20issue%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fcomments%2Fs7-26-18%2Fs72618-5177722-183507.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Nasdaq%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20three-quarters%20of%20the%20180%20companies%20it%20surveyed%20favored%20a%20switch%20to%20semi-annual%20reporting%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey%20results%20posted%20to%20the%20SEC's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20companies%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20quarterly%20earnings%20can%20feel%20steep.%20Preparing%20a%20single%20release%20can%20take%20weeks%20and%20pull%20in%20dozens%20of%20people%20across%20legal%2C%20accounting%2C%20and%20communications%20teams.%20But%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20earnings%20doesn't%20just%20disappear.%20It%20underwrites%20thousands%20of%20white-collar%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20roles%20now%20under%20pressure%20from%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20a%20slowing%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20were%20to%20get%20their%20way%2C%20what%20would%20it%20mean%20for%20the%20legions%20of%20white-collar%20professionals%20helping%20prop%20up%20the%20earnings%20ecosystem%2C%20from%20investor%20relations%20professionals%20to%20finance%20data%20providers%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20answer%20this%20question%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20people%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20process%20and%20reviewed%20comments%20made%20by%20companies%20and%20professional%20associations%20in%20response%20to%20the%20SEC's%202019%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20fewer%20earnings%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20what%20we%20learned%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216bb5def-9868-46ba-b5f0-cc556499791d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELess%20reporting%20doesn't%20mean%20less%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestor%20relations%20and%20communications%20professionals%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20quarterly%20earnings%20by%20making%20sure%20a%20company's%20story%20%E2%80%94%20financial%20results%2C%20growth%20prospects%2C%20risks%2C%20and%20strategy%20%E2%80%94%20is%20clearly%20conveyed%20to%20investors%2C%20analysts%2C%20regulators%2C%20and%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReducing%20earnings%2C%20however%2C%20might%20not%20ease%20their%20jobs%2C%20said%20Matthew%20Brusch%2C%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20NIRI%2C%20an%20association%20for%20investor%20relations%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestors%20won't%20simply%20just%20stop%20asking%20for%20the%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brusch%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20in%20IR.%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20experience%2C%20investors%20never%20want%20less%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20expects%20many%20companies%20would%20continue%20to%20report%20earnings%20quarterly%20even%20if%20given%20the%20opportunity%20to%20report%20just%20twice%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20a%20change%20might%20even%20add%20value%20to%20people%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20break%20into%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20Wall%20Street%20equity%20research%20analysts%2C%20who%20make%20stock%20recommendations.%20A%202018%20survey%20by%20the%20CFA%20Institute%20found%20that%2082%25%20of%20investor%20respondents%20strongly%20agreed%20that%20they%20would%20%26quot%3Bstruggle%20to%20locate%20information%26quot%3B%20if%20earnings%20reporting%20requirements%20were%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20investors%20surveyed%20also%20agreed%20that%20the%20benefits%20of%20quarterly%20earnings%20outweighed%20the%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221544%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c9d793183847aa39d6e743%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22998%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20from%20the%20CFA%20Institute%20survey%3Cp%3EScreenshot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b38fe5f3-8e52-413b-b566-8708ca9dec28%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuarterly%20earnings%20could%20be%20here%20to%20stay%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETheoretically%2C%20the%20biggest%20beneficiaries%20of%20fewer%20earnings%20reports%20would%20be%20C-Suite%20executives%2C%20like%20the%20CEO%20and%20CFO%2C%20who%20would%20have%20more%20time%20to%20focus%20on%20operations%2C%20capital%20raising%2C%20and%20other%20big-picture%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENasdaq's%202019%20survey%20showed%20that%20the%20average%20company%20said%20it%20spent%20about%20852.95%20hours%20a%20quarter%20on%20earnings.%20That's%20more%20than%20two%20weeks%20per%20person%20per%20quarter%2C%20assuming%20a%2010-person%20team.%20Reducing%20corporate%20earnings%20to%20just%20twice%20a%20year%20would%20therefore%20give%20the%20average%20executive%20an%20entire%20month%20back%20in%20time%20that%20could%20be%20spent%20on%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20said%20they%20don't%20see%20it%20playing%20out%20this%20way%2C%20however.%20They%20pointed%20to%20the%20EU%20and%20other%20regions%20where%20many%20companies%20continue%20to%20report%20earnings%20quarterly%20despite%20twice-a-year%20reporting%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20really%20think%20management's%20going%20to%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20just%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20report%20to%20the%20outside%2C%20I%20only%20want%20to%20look%20at%20my%20business%20every%20six%20months%3F'%26quot%3B%20%3Cspan%3ESandy%20Peters%2C%20senior%20head%20of%20global%20advocacy%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20the%20CFA%20Institute%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BProbably%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b39097a-bbed-41e1-a1c7-8f0996dcb640%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMost%20at%20risk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20losers%2C%20people%20said%2C%20may%20be%20for-hire%20professionals%20called%20in%20on%20an%20ad-hoc%20basis%20to%20help%20pull%20quarterly%20earnings%20together%2C%20including%20corporate%20lawyers%20and%20auditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20SEC's%202019%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fcomments%2Fs7-26-18%2Fs72618-5412063-184508.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESociety%20for%20Corporate%20Governance%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20a%20report%20showing%20that%20the%20costs%20associated%20with%20lawyers%20and%20accountants%20were%20among%20the%20most%20common%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSignificant%20diversion%20of%20legal%20and%20finance%2Faccounting%20team%20resources%2C%20plus%20expense%20of%20lawyers%20and%20accountants%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization's%20SEC%20filing%20said%2C%20quoting%20a%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAudit%20firm%20fees%26quot%3B%20ranked%20as%20a%20top%20cost%20of%20preparing%20earnings%20reports%20among%20the%20146%20members%20who%20responded%20to%20the%20organization's%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nasdaq%20survey%20said%20that%20companies%20reported%20paying%20an%20average%20of%20%24334%2C697.63%20a%20quarter%20on%20earnings%2C%20with%20at%20least%20one%20respondent%20citing%20quarterly%20costs%20as%20high%20as%20%247%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223ffd4bf4-5a11-4a6b-be74-ee31a6997f17%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERipple%20effects%20for%20data%20providers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReducing%20earnings%20requirements%20could%20also%20impact%20professionals%20who%20make%20money%20off%20them%2C%20including%20financial%20services%20data%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20LinkedIn%2C%20Daniel%20Goldberg%20asked%20colleagues%20in%20the%20alternative%20data%20world%20if%20a%20potential%20change%20would%20be%20good%20or%20bad%20for%20their%20industry.%20A%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20dozens%20of%20respondents%20thought%20the%20fewer%20corporate%20reports%20would%20mean%20more%20business%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20semi-annual%20reporting%2C%20the%20unmatched%20transparency%20of%20real-time%20data%20could%20spark%20a%20surge%20in%20alternative%20data%20adoption%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Goldberg%2C%20the%20former%20chief%20data%20strategy%20officer%20at%20Coresight%20Research%20who%20now%20works%20as%20an%20independent%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20a%20downside%20for%20an%20industry%20that's%20reliant%20on%20hedge%20funds%20for%20a%20sizeable%20chunk%20of%20its%20revenues%2C%20he%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFewer%20earnings%20events%20would%20mean%20fewer%20trading%20catalysts%20%E2%80%94%20a%20potential%20challenge%20for%20hedge%20funds%20chasing%20alpha%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Goldberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERado%20Lipus%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20data%20consultancy%20Neudata%2C%20said%20%26quot%3Bhedge%20funds%20are%20still%20very%20reliant%20on%20traditional%20products%20such%20as%20consensus%20estimates%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20plenty%20of%20alternative%20datasets%20use%20%26quot%3Bearnings%20calls%20as%20the%20input%20to%20create%20their%20product.%26quot%3B%20Ravenpack%2C%20an%20alternative%20data%20provider%2C%20has%20an%20earnings%20call%20analytics%20product%20that%20uses%20natural%20language%20processing%20tools%20to%20judge%20the%20sentiment%20of%20the%20executives%20speaking%20on%20a%20call%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20immediate%20impact%20of%20changing%20quarterly%20earnings%20could%20be%20to%20hedge%20funds%20themselves%2C%20said%20Marc%20Greenberg%2C%20a%20former%20executive%20at%20Steve%20Cohen's%20Point72%20who%20now%20runs%20a%20training%20firm%20called%20Greener%20Pastures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20best%20time%20of%20the%20year%20to%20make%20money%20as%20a%20hedge%20fund%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquarterly-earnings-trump-sec-accountants-lawyer-investor-relations-job-impact-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1758099841000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c9aa0457d362d375e84428%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquarterly-earnings-trump-sec-accountants-lawyer-investor-relations-job-impact-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Trump's%20call%20for%20fewer%20earnings%20reports%20stands%20to%20save%20publicly%20traded%20companies%20millions%2C%20including%20money%20spent%20on%20white-collar%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kwhitehouse%40insider.com%20(Kaja%20Whitehouse%2CBradley%20