he%20way%20the%20housing%20market%20shook%20out%20in%202022%20meant%20that%20we%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20sell%20our%20house%20in%20the%20Midwest%20at%20a%20strong%20profit.%20Though%20the%20four-bedroom%20house%20was%20older%2C%20it%20was%20still%20move-in-ready.%20We'd%20bought%20it%20for%20%2493%2C000%20in%202015%2C%20and%20after%20a%20%2419%2C000%20down%20payment%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20only%20costing%20us%20around%20%24800%20a%20month%20with%20taxes%2C%20mortgage%2C%20and%20insurance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-abroad-lowest-cost-of-living-highest-quality-of-life-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20costs%20were%20so%20low%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20save%20fairly%20aggressively%2C%20and%20we%20took%20advantage%20of%20that%20%E2%80%94%20partially%20because%20we%20knew%20that%2C%20if%20we%20ever%20had%20to%20move%2C%20we'd%20almost%20definitely%20experience%20higher%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d514cce-5124-4acb-8fb2-27cd017cb164%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20were%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20we%20loved%2C%20though%20it%20was%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20savings%20ended%20up%20being%20especially%20necessary%20when%20we%20realized%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-how-i-bought-home-new-york-city-apartment-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20rapidly%20changing%20market%20we%20were%20looking%20in%20would%20require%20more%20resources%20and%20quicker%20thinking%20than%20when%20we%20bought%20our%20first%20home.%20In%20early%202022%2C%20while%20we%20were%20relaxing%20on%20a%20Saturday%20morning%2C%20my%20husband%20showed%20me%20a%20listing%20for%20a%20house.%20The%20House.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20wasn't%20fancy%2C%20but%20it%20was%20perfectly%20located%2C%20had%20a%20huge%20yard%20for%20the%20area%2C%20and%20was%20all%20one%20story%2C%20which%20was%20nice%20with%20a%20toddler%20running%20around.%20The%20price%20was%20on%20the%20low%20side%20for%20the%20area%2C%20but%20it%20was%20%3Cem%3Estill%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20half-million-dollar%20house%3B%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20list%20price%20was%20%24500%2C000%20exactly.%20When%20we%20crunched%20the%20numbers%2C%20we%20figured%20out%20that%20this%20house%20would%20be%20doable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20we%20scaled%20back%20our%20savings%20rate%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fshould-i-sell-my-house-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esold%20our%20old%20house%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we%20could%20swing%20a%20solid%20down%20payment%20and%20pay%20the%20%242400%20a%20month%20housing%20costs.%20It%20would%20be%20a%20big%20lifestyle%20change%2C%20but%20we%20wanted%20to%20be%20close%20to%20family%20so%20badly.%20It%20felt%20like%20an%20investment%20in%20our%20mental%20health%20and%20community%20connection.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20sell%20the%20old%20house%20for%20%24176%2C000%2C%20buy%20the%20new%20house%20%E2%80%94%20there%20were%20multiple%20offers%2C%20and%20in%20the%20end%2C%20we%20got%20it%20for%20%24520%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20finally%20got%20ourselves%20back%20into%20an%20intergenerational%20community%20by%20mid-2022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b89a652-3056-466c-be11-0a4b82aac030%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20move%20was%20worth%20it%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe've%20now%20spent%20three%20years%20in%20this%20house%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20abundantly%20worthwhile.%20It's%20not%20just%20that%20I'm%20no%20longer%20chasing%20an%20active%20kiddo%20up%20and%20down%20stairs%2C%20though%20I%20do%20appreciate%20that%20frequently.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20son%20now%20gets%20to%20have%20dinner%20and%20play%20dates%20with%20his%20grandma%20every%20week%2C%20and%20at%20least%20one%20or%20two%20visits%20a%20month%20with%20his%20great-grandma%2C%20great-aunt%2C%20and%20great-uncle.%20We're%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-move-mountain-town-away-from-grandparents-struggle-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20a%20couple%20hours%20drive%20from%20my%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20too%2C%20leading%20to%20meet-in-the-middle%20meals%20and%20shared%20outings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAside%20from%20those%20visits%2C%20there%20have%20also%20been%20specific%20moments%20that%20have%20reminded%20me%20how%20deeply%20lucky%20we%20are%20to%20live%20here.%20When%20my%20son%20was%20hospitalized%20briefly%20with%20a%20bad%20case%20of%20RSV%2C%20we%20had%20family%20visitors%20at%20the%20hospital%20who%20picked%20up%20dinner%20for%20us%20and%20helped%20us%20get%20settled%20back%20in%20at%20home%20after%20a%20stressful%20couple%20of%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20my%20husband's%20great-uncle%20is%20out%20of%20town%2C%20my%20son%20and%20husband%20go%20over%20and%20feed%20the%20cats%20and%20explore%20his%20rural%20property%2C%20building%20my%20son's%20sense%20of%20responsibility%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-took-pay-cut-move-houston-boston-worth-it-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econnection%20to%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Surprise%20meetups%20for%20coffee%20or%20dinner%20are%20more%20affordable%20and%20fit%20naturally%20into%20our%20lives%3B%20when%20we%20lived%20hours%20away%2C%20just%20that%20much%20connection%20would%20necessitate%20tons%20of%20driving%20and%20hotel%20stays.%20These%20are%20little%20things%2C%20but%20every%20month%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20we%20more%20than%20get%20our%20money's%20worth%20for%20the%20tripled%20mortgage%20costs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20th