02020%20and%202021%2C%20just%2022%25%20of%20first-time%20buyers%20got%20help%20from%20family%20or%20friends%20in%202022%2C%20the%20lowest%20on%20record.%20The%20following%20year%20showed%20only%20a%20slight%20uptick%2C%20to%2023%25.%20Last%20year%2C%20just%20a%20quarter%20of%20first-timers%20got%20that%20kind%20of%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FJ1EbM%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FJ1EbM%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20of%20nepo%20buyers%20also%20coincides%20with%20another%20big%20shift%20in%20the%20makeup%20of%20new%20homeowners%3A%20First-time%20buyers%20are%20older%20and%20winning%20out%20with%20less%20frequency%20than%20ever%20before.%20NAR%20data%20shows%20that%20between%20June%202021%20and%20June%202022%2C%20the%20typical%20first-time%20buyer%20was%2036%2C%20the%20highest%20median%20age%20since%20NAR%20started%20tracking%20the%20figure%20in%201981.%20New%20homeowners%20accounted%20for%20a%20bit%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20home%20purchases%2C%20a%20record%20low.%20Things%20have%20only%20gotten%20worse.%20The%20typical%20age%20of%20a%20first-time%20homebuyer%20last%20year%20hit%20%3Cem%3Eanother%20%3C%2Fem%3Eall-time%20high%20of%2038%2C%20NAR%20data%20shows.%20First-time%20buyers'%20market%20share%20also%20shrank%20to%20a%20new%20low%20of%20just%2024%25%2C%20down%20from%2032%25%20the%20year%20prior.%20Perhaps%20unsurprisingly%2C%20buyers%20who%20made%20it%20through%20the%20door%20were%20better%20funded%20than%20in%20years%20past%20%E2%80%94%20the%20median%20household%20income%20of%20first-timers%20was%20%2497%2C000%2C%20a%20jump%20of%20%2426%2C000%20in%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FfaceX%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FfaceX%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20shifts%20help%20explain%20the%20nepo-buyer%20pullback.%20Family%20help%20is%20less%20common%20because%20the%20market%20is%20dominated%20by%20older%2C%20more%20independent%20buyers%20who%20can%20push%20forward%20despite%20the%20affordability%20challenges.%20Each%20year%20that%20prospective%20homeowners%20kick%20the%20can%20down%20the%20road%2C%20they%20grow%20less%20likely%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-millennials-gen-z-money-habits-parents-financial-help-spending-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eask%20for%20a%20family%20handout%3C%2Fa%3E.%20NAR%20found%20last%20year%20that%20younger%20millennials%2C%20which%20it%20defined%20as%20ages%2026%20to%2034%2C%20got%20gifts%20from%20family%20at%20about%20twice%20the%20rate%20of%20the%20elder%20cohort%2C%20ages%2035%20to%2044.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FiNpd7%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Dot%20Plot%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FiNpd7%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20more%20uncomfortable%20for%20someone%20who's%2038%20years%20old%2C%20which%20is%20the%20median%20age%20of%20today's%20first-time%20homebuyer%2C%20to%20ask%20for%20mom%20and%20dad's%20help%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Lautz%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20opposed%20to%20someone%20who%20is%20in%20their%20late%2020s%20or%20younger%2030s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20could%20have%20ripple%20effects%20throughout%20this%20cohort's%20entire%20lives.%20Older%20first-time%20homebuyers%20miss%20out%20on%20years%20of%20home-equity%20building%2C%20contributing%20to%20what%20Lautz%20often%20refers%20to%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20economy%20of%20'haves'%20and%20'have-nots.'%26quot%3B%20Instead%20of%20people%20embarking%20on%20their%20homeownership%20journey%20with%20a%20little%20help%20from%20their%20parents%2C%20they're%20staying%20put%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20it's%20a%20sign%20of%20buyer%20weakness%20when%20that%20gifting%20is%20pulling%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Black%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20noted%20in%20a%20recent%20story%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-remorse-cold-feet-purchase-cancellations-mortgage-rates-new-homes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomebuyers'%20cold%20feet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20that%20defined%20the%20early-COVID%20market%20has%20given%20way%20to%20a%20different%20flavor%20of%20FOMO.%20People%20are%20wary%20of%20taking%20the%20homebuying%20plunge%20given%20the%20state%20of%20the%20world%3A%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-hiring-unemployment-labor-force-participation-immigration-tariffs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%20is%20wobbling%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20executives%20pull%20back%20on%20hiring%20and%20warn%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-biggest-employers-facing-great-shrinking-corporations-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epermanently%20smaller%20headcounts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-wage-garnishment-paychecks-at-risk-default-collections-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStudent-loan%20delinquencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20spiking.%20In%20light%20of%20the%20staggering%20costs%20of%20homeownership%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20the%20housing%20research%20firm%20Zelman%20concluded%20that%20the%20rent-versus-buy%20math%20favors%20renting%20to%20a%20degree%20that%20hasn't%20been%20seen%20since%20the%20early%201980s.%20Prospective%20buyers%20may%20also%20be%20counting%20on%20borrowing%20rates%20to%20drop%20or%20sellers%20to%20slash%20prices%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20those%20on%20shakier%20ground%20hanging%20back%2C%20the%20buyers%20forging%20ahead%20are%20older%20and%20wealthier%20than%20at%20any%20point%20in%20more%20than%20four%20decades.%20They're%20relying%20more%20on%20their%20own%20investment%20accounts%20and%20less%20on%20the%20bank%20of%20mom%20and%20dad.%20The%20nepo%20buyer%20has%20taken%20a%20back%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20parents%20can%20pass%20along%20privilege%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20ways%20that%20aren't%20clear%20at%20the%20closing%20table.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-parent-planning-paying-kids-go-to-college-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPaying%20for%20college%20tuition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20say%2C%20can%20ensure%20their%20child%20graduates%20debt-free%20and%20ready%20to%20stack%20savings.%20Children%20whose%20parents%20are%20homeowners%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20end%20up%20buying%20a%20home%20themselves.%20A%20growing%20number%20of%20first-time%20buyers%20are%20moving%20straight%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-living-at-home-relying-on-parents-safety-net-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eout%20of%20their%20parents'%20places%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saving%20on%20rent%20before%20heading%20out%20on%20their%20own.%20Even%20homebuyers%20who%20don't%20get%20a%20financial%20handout%20may%20benefit%20from%20the%20advice%20and%20know-how%20of%20parents%20who%20have%20already%20weathered%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20cold%2C%20hard%20cash%20remains%20the%20simplest%20way%20to%20get%20a%20foothold%20in%20the%20market.%20That%20kind%20of%20help%20doesn't%20always%20equate%20to%20a%20free%20ride%2C%20though.%20Roughly%20a%20year%20after%20Frohling%20and%20her%20husband%20purchased%20the%20Illinois%20home%2C%20their%20daughter%20refinanced%20to%20pull%20equity%20out%20of%20the%20house%20to%20pay%20her%20parents%20back.%20The%20maneuver%20leaves%20a%20new%20loan%20attached%20to%20the%20place%2C%20which%20their%20daughter%20will%20now%20begin%20the%20long%20process%20of%20paying%20off%20%E2%80%94%20and%20building%20a%20nest%20egg%20of%20her%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20nepo%20buyers'%20numbers%20are%20down%2C%20they're%20far%20from%20extinct.%20Bill%20Mitchell%2C%20the%20loan%20officer%20who%20helped%20the%20Frohlings%20execute%20the%20refinance%2C%20says%20it's%20hard%20to%20overstate%20the%20power%20of%20a%20cash%20offer%20in%20a%20competitive%20market%20like%20Illinois%2C%20where%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-homes-unsold-economic-uncertainty-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erelative%20lack%20of%20homebuilding%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20available%20for%20sale%20is%20still%20tight.%20Mitchell%20estimates%20that%20about%2020%25%20of%20his%20clients%20use%20family%20money%20to%20beef%20up%20their%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20see%20that%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20see%20that%20I've%20got%20these%20clients%20that%20have%20made%20an%20offer%20on%20one%2C%20two%2C%20three%20homes%20and%20got%20beat%20out%20by%20cash%20offers%2C%20that's%20typically%20when%20I'll%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20let's%20think%20of%20potential%20alternative%20strategies%20here%2C'%26quot%3B%20Mitchell%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3B'Do%20you%20have%20family%20that%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20help%20out%20in%20a%20situation%20like%20this%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrohling%20says%20she%20initially%20worried%20she%20had%20robbed%20her%20daughter%20of%20the%20joy%20that%20comes%20with%20buying